{"id":"2209.04373","submitter":"Yanfang Mo","authors":"Yanfang Mo, Wei Chen, Keyou You, Li Qiu","title":"Optimal $(0,1)$-Matrix Completion with Majorization Ordered Objectives\n  (To the memory of Pravin Varaiya)","comments":"16pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"eess.SY cs.DM cs.SY math.OC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We propose and examine two optimal $(0,1)$-matrix completion problems with\nmajorization ordered objectives. They elevate the seminal study by Gale and\nRyser from feasibility to optimality in partial order programming (POP),\nreferring to optimization with partially ordered objectives. We showcase their\napplications in electric vehicle charging, portfolio optimization, and secure\ndata storage. Solving such integer POP (iPOP) problems is challenging because\nof the possible non-comparability among objective values and the integer\nrequirements. Nevertheless, we prove the essential uniqueness of all optimal\nobjective values and identify two particular ones for each of the two\ninherently symmetric iPOP problems. Furthermore, for every optimal objective\nvalue, we decompose the construction of an associated optimal~$(0,1)$-matrix\ninto a series of sorting processes, respectively agreeing with the rule of\nthumb \"peak shaving\" or \"valley filling.\" We show that the resulting algorithms\nhave linear time complexities and verify their empirical efficiency via\nnumerical simulations compared to the standard order-preserving method for POP.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Sep 2022 16:13:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-12"}
