\pm$0.084 d$^{-1}$). We subsequently\nidentified a few more frequencies that appear to be combinations of a $g$ or\n$p$ mode and one of the higher cited frequencies not due to pulsations. We\npropose that KIC 6951642 accommodates for a fast-rotating $\\gamma$ Dor-$\\delta$\nSct hybrid star with various rotationally split multiplets of $g$ and $p$ modes\nand that it also displays a cycle lasting years of (possible) stellar activity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 10 Sep 2022 12:40:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
